&#039;Mountain Battles&#039; is the fourth studio album by alt-rock
 group The Breeders.
 The album also marks the
 return of both Kim and Kelley Deal since 1993&#039;s &#039;Last 
Splash&#039;. Regarded by some to
 be one of the most unique alternative rock groups of the 90s,
 the band are best known for their melodic and off-kilter songs.
 The combination of memorable guitar hooks and Kim Deal&#039;s sweet
 vocals, perfectly encapsulate the band&#039;s strengths and individuality.
 Includes the single &#039;We&#039;re Gonna Rise&#039;.
